THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 277 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. If a tribal government wishes to enter into an agreement for joint or
4 cooperative action or contract with the governing body of a county or agency
5 thereof, pursuant to the provisions of this section and NRS 277.080 to 277.180,
6 inclusive, within which tribal land of the tribal government is located, partially or
7 wholly, for the performance of any governmental service, activity or undertaking
8 which the tribal government, county or agency thereof is authorized by law to
9 perform, the governing body of the county may, on behalf of the county or agency
10 thereof, engage in discussions in good faith with the tribal government for the
11 performance of such services.
12 2. If the governing body of a county or agency thereof enters into an
13 agreement or contract pursuant to the provisions of this section and NRS 277.080
14 to 277.180, inclusive, such an agreement must be a conditional interlocal
15 agreement which:
16 (a) Must not require a tribal government to waive sovereign immunity; and
17 (b) Must authorize the governing body of the county or agency thereof to
18 terminate the agreement by providing the tribal government with 90 days’
19 advance written notice, upon the occurrence of any of the following conditions:
20 (1) The tribal government is more than 60 days delinquent on its
21 financial obligations under the agreement;
22 (2) The tribal government fails to respond for more than 90 days to a
23 written demand by the governing body of the county or agency thereof to perform
24 under the agreement;
25 (3) An authorized representative of the tribal government or tribal
26 council or tribal police of the tribal government prevents entry onto the tribal
27 land or otherwise prevents the county or agency thereof, or any employee or
28 agent of the county or agency, from otherwise performing under the agreement;
29 or
30 (4) The tribal government enters into any subsequent agreement
31 pursuant to this section and NRS 277.080 to 277.180, inclusive, which materially
32 conflicts with the existing agreement.
33 3. For the purposes of this section, an agency of a county does not include
34 any water authority, water district or water reclamation district.
35 4. As used in this section:
36 (a) “Good faith” means honesty in fact and the observance of reasonable
37 standards of fair dealing.
38 (b) “Tribal government” means the governing body of an Indian tribe, group
39 of tribes, organized segment of a tribe or any organization representing two or
40 more such entities.
41 Sec. 2. NRS 277.080 is hereby amended to read as follows:
42 277.080 NRS 277.080 to 277.180, inclusive, and section 1 of this act may be
43 cited as the Interlocal Cooperation Act.
44 Sec. 3. NRS 277.090 is hereby amended to read as follows:
45 277.090 It is the purpose of NRS 277.080 to 277.180, inclusive, and section 1
46 of this act to permit local governments to make the most efficient use of their
47 powers by enabling them to cooperate with other local governments on a basis of
48 mutual advantage and thereby to provide services and facilities in a manner and
49 pursuant to forms of governmental organization which will best accord with

